x\ge y
\displaystyle(x,y)=\frac{x+y}2+\frac{|x-y|}2
x\ge y,
(x,y)=x
|x-y|=x-y\implies \frac{x+y}2+\frac{|x-y|}2=\frac{x+y+(x-y)}2=x
x<y,
(x,y)=y
|x-y|=-(x-y)\implies \frac{x+y}2+\frac{|x-y|}2=\frac{x+y-(x-y)}2=y
\max(x,y)=\frac{|x-y|+x+y}2
